Creating user account :
 
 The command to create user account is useradd.
	For Example:
		Useradd user_name(user1)

	The user account is now created . the user account record will be in the file /etc/passwd as below
	user1:x:500:500::/home/user1:/bin/bash

	username:Passwd(encrypted):userid:groupid:commands:homedirectory:shellfor the user
  
Setting Password: 
	The command passwd will be used to set password for any user. The same command will change the passwd of this user.
Command: Passwd User_name

Modifying the user account:
The command used to modify user parameters is usermod
For example:
  
Change the userid
 usermod â€“u changeuserid username
		
Change the group	
  usermod -g changegroupname username

Change the home directoy
	usermod -d changehomedirctory username
    
Deleting user account:
	command: userdel

Creating group accounts:
	groupadd group_name

Modifying group accounts:
	groupmod old_name new_name

Deleting group accounts:
	groupdel group_name
  
Configurations files
  
 Authentication information is stored in plain text files:

	/etc/passwd
	/etc/shadow
	/etc/group
	/etc/gshadow









